The paper deals with online graph matching problems, which are typically studied in the computer science subfield of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves game theory (cs.GT) in the form of competitive analysis of algorithms. Additionally, the paper discusses load balancing (cs.AL), which is a common application of online graph matching. Information theory (cs.IT) is also mentioned in the context of the weighted matching problem. Finally, the paper involves combinatorial optimization (cs.DM) in the form of finding maximum cardinality matchings.
